The Party's locals fill with maté and grief and the best-trained Marxists the continent has produced: MIR cadres who know clandestinity like a trade, UP economists who ran ministries, printers who set type through artillery. The study circles will never recover, in the best sense. The DFS photographs the doorways and begins a whole new wing of the archive, cross-referenced by accent.

@discreta
on-arrival: exiliados += 1; political_capital += 1

Beds are found, quietly; two printers get work; the Party marches in the great solidarity acts without organizing them. It is proportionate and defensible, and years later, when the Southern Cone teaches its hardest seminars — on how organizations die, and how they survive dying — you will have bought the student rate at the door instead of a seat at the table.
